caption: My favorite spot to eat at! Quick & delicious & great customer service
Best Orange chicken In the state of Maryland 💯 bubble tea also fire 🔥 you won’t be disappointed
I eat here a lot since I work in the area. I like how the service is always awesome and they keep the place well kept consistently. Pricing is convenient and they serve sizeable portions.

Ordered this item through GrubHub. The communication was poor and items were incorrect. The establishment clearly did not care. Also I found hair in the food. That addition was lovely to say the least...
staff was super friendly & helpful! orange chicken & boba tea is very good, 10/10
Authentic food that totally helped with my homesickness. Though I feel the food is more like Hong Kong for than Taiwanese, which was exactly what I wanted.  Excellent friendly service as well.
Chinese food... yummy. I give this spot two thumbs up. I'll return family next time. The bill was decent for the quality.
Best real orange chicken in the city hidden gem milk tea amazing I had my fam with me I hype it up he told you was right THE HYPE Is REAL
Good place for chinese food. This place is absolutely one of my favorites. Service is typically above par. It has a good feel to it. Feels like a place in Charlotte that I enjoyed visiting.
Chinese food, my preferred treat. Staff treated us so nice. Prices were fair.
One of my preferred places for tasty chinese food. the staff was very welcoming and sociable. bring your appetite because portions are filling. i see why this place has so many good reviews.

Delicious food , Kind staff and quick service . It is authentic Chinese / Taiwanese food ! It was difficult to find Good Chinese food in Baltimore and I’m glad I found this place , reminds me of the delicious food I ate in Shanghai  . And we absolutely love their boba tea !
An unassuming restaurant in a food court in the middle of downtown Baltimore. In a city with very little good Chinese/Taiwanese food, the beef noodle soup and milk tea are amazing here!

Chinese food in Baltimore is pretty bad, so it's nice to come across a place with good home-style Taiwanese food. You can get a decent bowl of noodles here with egg marinated in soy sauce (even has the seaweed tied in a knot) and the boba is delicious and highly customizable in sweetness. The staff are as sweet as can be. It's a little hard to find because it's in the food court tucked into the plaza, but there were plenty of people finding it just fine on a Saturday afternoon. I'll definitely be back.

Being from Southern California where there are alot of boba shops, this spot was a great hidden jewel. I've tried their popcorn chicken with the braised minced meat. My friend tried their orange chicken and both food was really great. I also ordered a passionfruit tea and it is up to par to my favorite boba shops back home. On a different visit I had the chicken again but with curry rice and a taro slushy. Taro slushy could be better but the chicken doesn't disappoint. The price is on the high side but still affordable. Will definitely be an occasional treat for me to go here.
Phenom Customer service and DELICIOUS Food!!!!

The chicken was ok, a bit too salty. The rice was not hot enough, feels like it was warmed by microwave, some areas that were not heated enough were a bit hard to chew. Overall ok to have your tummy full, but definitely not worth 4.0+ rating.
Always cheerful and helpful! Their boba tea is the best!
Best bubble tea around.  Boba is nice and soft not hard like other joints. food great, staff super nice. great place.

My first time there and the staff was super friendly, helpful, and quick servicing. I only got Bubble Teas but they were delicious; highly recommend the Passionfruit Tea (which has coconut jelly and boba in it) if you like fruity tea and the WinterMelon Tea if you like sweet tea with just a hint of fruit flavor. The bobas also had the right amount of toothsome chewiness. I also liked that you could customize the amount of sugar and ice added per drink.  These tea's were perfect for a dairy-free option but if you did want a creamy boba you could sub out the regular milk for soy milk.
Super delightful Chinese place with some classics like orange chicken and some more unique choices. Really sweet, pleasant, and incredibly helpful staff. Cool Boba tea!
Great food and very polite staff
Best place in downtown for boba and taiwanese food
Delicious boba milk tea and tea eggs. We love it. The lady at the counter is super sweet. She customized the sugar, tea and ice for our single order.
The coffee milk tea was really good and the boba was soft and chewy, how I like it. Would come again. The women at the counter was super sweet and friendly. Service was also very fast.
I love eating here. The servers are respectful and very accommodating to customers. The food is great a d the atmosphere is wonderful in this area.
Very good Chinese restaurant
Especially for it being our first time, service was phenomenal. Very friendly and fast. Wide variety of food options and tasted great!
Foods are tasty but expensive.
Too expensive
Taste ok . Can be better.
Best boba in Baltimore! The staff is kind and will always make your day with smiles and kindness
Pretty decent bubble tea and food.
Cool lunch place for work. Orange chicken lunch special was good. Staff was nice and fast.
Excellent made to order drinks (non alcoholic) and excellent (if limited) menu. Beef soup is great and so is the orange chicken, which is their signature dish! And Diana has a great memory for names.
Food Hit like a Bit.....Orange chicken  and broccoli is slapping
So glad to finally have a Taiwanese restaurant here
Bubble tea was delicious!
Nice semi casual Chinese place in Chinatown with good food and low prices, large menu so ou can choose whatever, great appetizers.
They have a great selection of bubble teas. The yogurt jasmine tea is my favorite!
Ok
I loved their Taiwanese popcorn chicken and minced pork rice, and they boba is the BEST. Overall, an amazing, authentic, and super rare fast food Taiwanese restaurant in Baltimore!
It was great! Loved the deep fried mochi
Very friendly, genuine people running this place. Food was at a reasonable price as well.
Great place to have food of Taiwan!

This place is awesome.  Real chinese food, not american.  The bubble tea is really good, you can customize your order and they have a satisfaction guarantee, if you don't like they will make you another.  I have never been disappointed.  The angel hair soup is so flavorful and the curry is very flavorful.  You won't be left hungry!

This place is a corner of surprise heaven.  The staff is incredibly nice and their service is traditional and professional.  Their food is fresher and juicier than anything I've had in the last many months. And the prices are appropriate! It might not be what many people are used to, but I can't believe they aren't more popular!  I got the Jasmine green milk tea with sesame pudding and boba. And order number E4 the Stew Chicken Minced Pork Rice.  A single meal is at LEAST 3 servings.  I recommend trying the exploding boba pearls or the pudding! I've never seen that somewhere else before.  Girlfriend tried their nuggets which were fried but very juicy!!
Their bubble tea is underrated in my opinion! Would recommend :)
Excellent food! The people here are sooo friendly!! This will be a regular spot for me!
Super friendly cashiers and wonderful service!  Would comrcome back againagain .👌

My husband tried their orange chicken and both food was really great. I also ordered a passionfruit tea and it is up to par to my favorite boba shops back home. On a different visit I had the chicken again but with curry rice and a taro slushy. Taro slushy could be better but the chicken doesn't disappoint. The price is on the high side but still affordable. Will definitely be an occasional treat for me to go here.
The staff here are remarkably kind and cheerful! I had the beef noodle soup and it was delicious. I also loved the bubble tea and came back to have another!
BEST BOBA TEA IN THE CITY hands down!
Food was half done
I love this place! Friendly service and great food! They've got my loyalty!
The food at WOW Food Cafe was delicious and the staff there were so kind and helpful. The Boba Tea there was so good highly recommend!
One of the better chinese food in Baltimore. Selection is limited, but what they have is good. It tastes like real chinese food.
Kind and very nice staff
Best service and boba in Baltimore!  The staff always welcomes me and my fiancé with a warm smile.  Seriously the best :D
Extremely helpful and kind staff. The food was delicious, we ordered the golden shrimp with curry rice, fries and mochi. The grapefruit jasmine club is sensational!
Closed due to weather? It only snowed a half an inch... but it was a two days before New Year.   :-/

The service was excellent and the food was exquisite. I ordered the orange chicken lunch special; it was not only the best orange chicken I've ever had, it was probably the best lunch I've ever had. I have never received this much satisfaction from a $9 purchase.
Authentic Chinese home cooking. The boba is delicious and they are the nicest possible people. A great place to eat if you're in the area.
The boba tea is always amazing and the staff is always super kind.
Nice food,  friendly staff!

The people who work here are so kind & helpful, and the bubble tea is fabulous. They have a punch card for frequent tea drinkers, too. I am thrilled to be working nearby such a great little food stand. I haven't tried anything but tea yet, but I will soon!

I've tried the beef noodle soup and the chicken and rice as well as the boba tea. I feel like both dishes are a little bland for my taste, and the boba tea was too sweet, but to each their own. The employees are always super polite and cheery, which I do appreciate.
Great bubble tea but on the expensive side.
Great bubble tea.
Great place. Service was excellent. Might be my first time but definitely not the last.
Love it, eat here once a week!

THE BEST BUBBLE TEA !!!!!!!!!!!! Seriously, they have the best bubble tea. And everyone there is so polite and nice to me. I even tip sometimes. The food is great, best orange chicken I ever had. Maybe a little overpriced (just the food). But is definitely my favorite place around here. I have one of those stamps cards that I completed already and I am about to complete the second one! I LOVE WOW food!
Really nice employees.  Food was good.

Nestled within the Charles EATS Plaza you can find this hidden jewel among other tasty shops that are easy to miss if you are not familiar with the area. This place has quickly become my new favorite lunch spot. I go there for the juicy, crispy, hot and sweet nuggets of orange chicken, but most go for their bubble tea. It's certainly one of the better places to find bubble tea within the city. They use real tea leaves not the powdered tea mix. You can customize your bubble tea by specifying the sweetness level and the amount of ice. Well worth checking out if you're in the area.
Wow Food Cafe has perfectly cooked boba served in actual brewed tea, something that is often hard to find in Baltimore. Service is very friendly and efficient. I rarely pass up a chance to stop by.
Good, fast Chinese food with polite service.
Good food and Boba. The chicken was good but was a little bland
I had bubble tea and the beef noodle soup. Both were delicuous.  Can't wait to go back and try other menu items I haven't had before. From what I can tell, this is a legit Taiwanese place.
Excellent, attentive service and bubble tea was very good!
